<br>
Here's a link hope it helps.  It's been a long long time since I did vox so it may be out of date but I did touch it up with some of the newer 50-52 spells.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.trafficblast.com/drinal/lott_vox_raid.html">www.trafficblast.com/drin..._raid.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Camping out saves a lot of frustration.  We even started making buffin ggroups with the bards and just buffed people one at a time and sending them to chat to wait for everyone else.<br>
<br>
On Naggy you can even buff speed after you leave chat if you want since Enchanters don't do much but Tash on him.<br>
<br>
I liked to do dragons with lvl50+ only.  24 is a fun fight. I never got to try it with 18 before I hit 53, definitely possible with all the new weapons and buffs.  <br>
I suggest you Bring 30 or 36 if you want a guaranteed victory.  Being feared pretty much stops when you get to 51.<br>
<br>
I never did make a naggy guide since he's just a straight fight with no real coordination needed =)  There's a warrior with AE.. kill it=)  <br>
<br>
With the new circle of winter/summer spells I guess you would want to buff 5 at a time now. You'll have to work that out =) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ugozaro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gozaro</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.trafficblast.com/lott/data/gozaro_head.jpg BORDER=0> at: 6/6/01 11:36:08 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ufflewddurfflam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fflewddur Fflam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#993300>(6/6/01 1:47:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy and Vox buffing.</span><hr size=1> Buffing for Vox/Naggy is simple.  You start with four useless buffs that will be the first dispelled.  Then you go for stat buffs, clarity, cleric/shaman hp/ac buffs, resists, and haste, pre.  Set it up initially so that each group has 5 members in it so that enchanters and druids can easily be passed from party to party for resists.  <br>
<br>
-FF <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ugozaro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gozaro</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.trafficblast.com/lott/data/gozaro_head.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#993300>(6/6/01 2:29:41 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy and Vox buffing.</span><hr size=1> If it was so simple all the pickup raids wouldn't be telling horror stories.   <br>
<br>
Simple the 3rd or 4th time sure, but on pick up raids when you have new leaders, new raiders they need something 100% full proof.  <br>
<br>
camping to chat takes all the trouble away from buffing and we all know it's the buffing part that takes so long.<br>
<br>
I also recommend if you use this method that aside from clarity and speed everyone should get every buff.  you'll have much better success if everyone has symbol and rune and all shaman/AC buffs.  Even those wizards. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uwysteriaplushfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wysteria Plushfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#993300>(6/6/01 2:47:35 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy and Vox buffing.</span><hr size=1> Maybe Naggy and Vox are different from Faydedar (the one pick-up naggy raid I attended was so horrible I wouldn't go to another) but I always end up with zero buffs after a Faydedar fight.  My MR isn't hugely great, but it isn't horrible either.  Probably in the 150-180 range after buffs.<br>
<br>
The camp-out idea is good.  First I ever heard of it was a week or so ago.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udocnurse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Docnurse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#993300>(6/6/01 3:24:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy and Vox buffing.</span><hr size=1> only reason there would be horror stories is because people dont buff when they are suppost to and dont listen. If you are taking down any mob that requires large amounts of people either listen to the leader or go away simple as that. If people listen and follow instructions there should be no problems at all, if you dont listen and follow then your raid is doomed and hope you enjoy 3 hours of CR.<br>
<br>
Enursin<br>
<br>
Just listen to the leader !!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ubargeroth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bargeroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 165<br> <font color=#993300>(6/6/01 3:37:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy and Vox buffing.</span><hr size=1> When ever I get a tell from someone saying a naggy/vox raid failed it was due to :<br>
<br>
lack of experience<br>
Lack of levels<br>
lack of resist gear (90% of the time).<br>
<br>
Gozaro's sugestion is still a good one for any first time naggy/vox leaders. it takes time to explain to folks what your gonna do. Sending them to chat buys you time so at least your buffs dont fade. Then youll just die becuase of lack of levels and gear ).<br>
<br>
Bargeroth<br>
